The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, specifically the density of subgraphs of halved cubes and Johnson graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and graph theory (cs.GT).
